<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">BUTTON_RIGHT .equ #00000001b<br />BUTTON_LEFT&nbsp; .equ #00000010b<br />BUTTON_DOWN&nbsp; .equ #00000100b<br />BUTTON_UP&nbsp; &nbsp; .equ #00001000b<br />BUTTON_START .equ #00010000b<br />BUTTON_SELECT equ #00100000b<br />BUTTON_B&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;.equ #01000000b<br />BUTTON_A&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;.equ #10000000b</div>
<br />(They're in the wrong order but that doesn't matter <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" />.)  The <span style="color: violet">ROL</span> started to work right... kindof, <span style="color: red">Select</span>, <span style="color: red">Start</span>, <span style="color: red">B</span>, and <span style="color: red">A</span> worked now. And now the other half doesn't work... It's the same problem on BOTH <span style="color: violet">ROL AND ROR</span>!  <img src="./images/smilies/icon_biggrin.gif" alt=":D" title="Very Happy" />  <span style="color: red">Select</span> doesn't play the famitone song, but it does fix whatever is wrong with my controller reading code.   After pressing <span style="color: red">select</span> all the buttons do something.  <img src="./images/smilies/icon_confused.gif" alt=":?" title="Confused" /></div>

