				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">He's making the RAM in "pages" of 256.
<br />
<br />Page 0=$0000-$00FF
<br />Page 1=$0100-$01FF
<br />
<br />And so on. Page 1 is the stck area, it's hard wired. Phen you put something on it, it DE-INCREMENTS the stack. So when you load the stack with FF (LDX #$FF, TXS) it's at the highest point. Most people don't use all of the stack, so sometimes random variables go into the unused space, despite the stack being there. I don't put any there myself, but if I need to, they're going there. I doubt I'll need it though. <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /></div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

